mil.nga.giat.geowave.ingest

Interface IngestPluginBase<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The type for the input data
    O - The type that represents each data entry being ingested
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataAdapterProvider<O>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IngestWithMapper<I,O>, LocalFileIngestPlugin<O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GeoLifeIngestPlugin, GeoLifeIngestPlugin.IngestGeoLifeFromHdfs, GeoToolsRasterDataStoreIngestPlugin, GeoToolsVectorDataStoreIngestPlugin, GpxIngestPlugin, GpxIngestPlugin.IngestGpxTrackFromHdfs, TdriveIngestPlugin, TdriveIngestPlugin.IngestGpxTrackFromHdfs

    public interface IngestPluginBase<I,O>
extends DataAdapterProvider<O>
    An interface required for ingest plugins to implement a conversion from an expected input format to GeoWave data which can in turn be ingested into the system.

    • Method Detail

      • toGeoWaveData

        CloseableIterator<GeoWaveData<O>> toGeoWaveData(I input,
                                              ByteArrayId primaryIndexId,
                                              String globalVisibility)
        Convert from an expected input format to a data format that can be directly ingested into GeoWave
        Parameters:
        input - The expected input.
        primaryIndexId - The index ID specified via a commandline argument (this is typically either the default spatial index or default spatial-temporal index)
        globalVisibility - If on the command-line the user specifies a global visibility to write to the visibility column in GeoWave, it is passed along here. It is assumed that this is the same visibility string that will be passed to DataAdapterProvider.getDataAdapters()
        Returns:
        The objects that can be directly ingested into GeoWave
